[[cdo:5 nguŏk 6 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:5 goe̍h 6 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:五月初六]] {{Lunisolar May}} '''May 6''' is the 6th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1607]] {{ill|June 29|ja|6月29日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – A Korean envoy visited Edo for the first time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.com|title=Reference needed|accessdate=2021-04}}</ref> * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1865]] {{ill|June 28|ja|6月28日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Under the mediation of Sakamoto Ryōma, negotiations with the Chōshū Domain led to the initial formation of the Satsuma–Chōshū Alliance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.com|title=Reference needed|accessdate=2021-04}}</ref>
== Births == * [[承和 (日本)|Shōwa]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[835]] {{ill|June 5|ja|6月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Heira Hiro, one of the four sons of Hira Takamochi of the Kantō Taira clan (died [[928]]). * [[応保]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1162]] {{ill|June 20|ja|6月20日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Benchō, a monk of the Jōdo-shū (died [[1238]]).
== Deaths == * [[Emperor Jomei]] 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[635]] {{ill|May 27|ja|5月27日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor Jomei, the first emperor of the Tang dynasty of Japan (also known as Li Yuan, the founding emperor of the Tang in China; born [[566]]). * {{ill|Tenpyō-hōji|ja|天平宝字|12=draft|12=draft}} 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[763]] {{ill|June 21|ja|6月21日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – the great monk {{ill|Ganjin|ja|鑑真|12=draft|12=draft}}, a prominent Chinese Buddhist monk who founded the Japanese Ritsu school (born [[688]]). * [[Ōei]] 15th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1408]] {{ill|May 31|ja|5月31日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Ashikaga Yoshimitsu, the 3rd shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[1358]]). * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1587]] {{ill|June 11|ja|6月11日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Otomo Sōrin, a Sengoku daimyō of Bungo (born [[1530]]). * [[Keichō]] 17th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1612]] {{ill|June 5|ja|6月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Arima Harunobu, a Christian daimyō (born [[1567]]). * [[Genroku]] 7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1694]] {{ill|May 29|ja|5月29日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Mitsui Takatoshi, the progenitor of the Mitsui family, a prominent merchant (born [[1622]]).
