== Births == * [[承和 (日本)|Shōwa]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[835]] {{ill|June 5|ja|6月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Heira Hiro, one of the four sons of Hira Takamochi of the Kantō Taira clan (died [[928]]). * [[応保]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1162]] {{ill|June 20|ja|6月20日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Benchō, a monk of the Jōdo-shū (died [[1238]]).
== Deaths == * [[Emperor Jomei]] 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[635]] {{ill|May 27|ja|5月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor Jomei, the first emperor of the Tang dynasty of Japan (also known as Li Yuan, the founding emperor of the Tang in China; born [[566]]). * {{ill|Tenpyō-hōji|ja|天平宝字|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[763]] {{ill|June 21|ja|6月21日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – the great monk {{ill|Ganjin|ja|鑑真|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a prominent Chinese Buddhist monk who founded the Japanese Ritsu school (born [[688]]). * [[Ōei]] 15th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1408]] {{ill|May 31|ja|5月31日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Ashikaga Yoshimitsu, the 3rd shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[1358]]). * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1587]] {{ill|June 11|ja|6月11日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Otomo Sōrin, a Sengoku daimyō of Bungo (born [[1530]]). * [[Keichō]] 17th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1612]] {{ill|June 5|ja|6月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Arima Harunobu, a Christian daimyō (born [[1567]]). * [[Genroku]] 7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1694]] {{ill|May 29|ja|5月29日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Mitsui Takatoshi, the progenitor of the Mitsui family, a prominent merchant (born [[1622]]).
