{{Not to be confused with|May 6|qq=May 6}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月初六|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 6일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 6''' is the 6th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1607]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – A Korean envoy visited Edo for the first time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.com|title=Reference needed|accessdate=2021-04|qq=}}</ref> * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 1st year (leap May) ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1865]] [[:en:June 28|June 28]]) – Under the mediation of Sakamoto Ryōma, negotiations with the Chōshū Domain led to the initial formation of the Satsuma–Chōshū Alliance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.com|title=Reference needed|accessdate=2021-04|qq=}}</ref>
== Births == * [[承和 (日本)|Shōwa]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[835]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – Heira Hiro, one of the four sons of Hira Takamochi of the Kantō Taira clan (died [[928]]). * [[応保]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1162|1162]] [[:en:June 20|June 20]]) – Benchō, a monk of the Jōdo-shū (died [[:en:1238|1238]]).
== Deaths == * [[Emperor Jomei]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[635]] [[:en:May 27|May 27]]) – Emperor Jomei, the first emperor of the Tang dynasty of Japan (also known as Li Yuan, the founding emperor of the Tang in China; born [[566]]). * [[:en:Tenpyō-hōji|Tenpyō-hōji]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[763]] [[:en:June 21|June 21]]) – the great monk [[:en:Jianzhen|Ganjin]], a prominent Chinese Buddhist monk who founded the Japanese Ritsu school (born [[688]]). * [[Ōei]] 15th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1408|1408]] [[:en:May 31|May 31]]) – Ashikaga Yoshimitsu, the 3rd shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[:en:1358|1358]]). * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1587]] [[:en:June 11|June 11]]) – Otomo Sōrin, a Sengoku daimyō of Bungo (born [[1530]]). * [[Keichō]] 17th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1612]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – Arima Harunobu, a Christian daimyō (born [[1567]]). * [[Genroku]] 7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1694]] [[:en:May 29|May 29]]) – Mitsui Takatoshi, the progenitor of the Mitsui family, a prominent merchant (born [[1622]]).
