== Births == * [[承和 (日本)|Shōwa]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[835]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – Heira Hiro, one of the four sons of Hira Takamochi of the Kantō Taira clan (died [[928]]). * [[応保]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1162|1162]] [[:en:June 20|June 20]]) – Benchō, a monk of the Jōdo-shū (died [[:en:1238|1238]]).
== Deaths == * [[Emperor Jomei]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[635]] [[:en:May 27|May 27]]) – Emperor Jomei, the first emperor of the Tang dynasty of Japan (also known as Li Yuan, the founding emperor of the Tang in China; born [[566]]). * [[:en:Tenpyō-hōji|Tenpyō-hōji]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[763]] [[:en:June 21|June 21]]) – the great monk [[:en:Jianzhen|Ganjin]], a prominent Chinese Buddhist monk who founded the Japanese Ritsu school (born [[688]]). * [[Ōei]] 15th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1408|1408]] [[:en:May 31|May 31]]) – Ashikaga Yoshimitsu, the 3rd shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[:en:1358|1358]]). * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1587|1587]] [[:en:June 11|June 11]]) – Otomo Sōrin, a Sengoku daimyō of Bungo (born [[:en:1530|1530]]). * [[Keichō]] 17th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1612]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – Arima Harunobu, a Christian daimyō (born [[:en:1567|1567]]). * [[Genroku]] 7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1694]] [[:en:May 29|May 29]]) – Mitsui Takatoshi, the progenitor of the Mitsui family, a prominent merchant (born [[1622]]).
